1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:02,961
You've been touching your clothes for a while.

2
00:00:03,086 --> 00:00:04,713
Are you uncomfortable somewhere?

3
00:00:06,631 --> 00:00:09,342
I was just gathering my thoughts.

4
00:00:09,342 --> 00:00:12,679
It's a suit lent to me by someone who recognized my strengths.

5
00:00:13,054 --> 00:00:15,015
Someone who recognized your strengths?

6
00:00:15,181 --> 00:00:15,932
Yes.

7
00:00:16,516 --> 00:00:18,351
Like this stiffly starched shirt collar,

8
00:00:18,351 --> 00:00:20,186
he gave me the courage not to be intimidated

9
00:00:20,186 --> 00:00:21,980
in front of the interviewer.

10
00:00:22,105 --> 00:00:25,900
He reminded me of the importance of my strengths and prudence.

11
00:00:26,484 --> 00:00:28,737
Thanks to that, without feeling intimidated,

12
00:00:28,737 --> 00:00:31,197
I was able to answer confidently in front of you.

13
00:00:31,406 --> 00:00:32,782
Because I have to earn the worth of these clothes.

14
00:00:33,366 --> 00:00:34,242
Interesting.

15
00:00:34,617 --> 00:00:35,577
But even if you were wearing your own clothes,

16
00:00:35,577 --> 00:00:37,203
would you still have that kind of nerve?

17
00:00:37,412 --> 00:00:37,912
Excuse me?

18
00:00:38,288 --> 00:00:39,372
You may go.

19
00:00:39,372 --> 00:00:40,457
You will hear good news.

20
00:00:41,791 --> 00:00:43,209
Yes, sir.

21
00:00:44,252 --> 00:00:45,879
Thank you.

22
00:00:51,593 --> 00:00:53,845
I like his spirit.

23
00:01:13,073 --> 00:01:16,659
(Job Acceptance Text Message)

24
00:01:23,750 --> 00:01:25,251
Oh, Hyung!

25
00:01:25,251 --> 00:01:25,960
Huh?

26
00:01:25,960 --> 00:01:27,670
I passed!

27
00:01:29,631 --> 00:01:31,633
You passed?

28
00:01:32,801 --> 00:01:35,136
I told you it would work out.

29
00:01:41,059 --> 00:01:42,894
What is that?

30
00:01:46,022 --> 00:01:48,525
I was thinking of leaving Seoul for a while.

31
00:01:50,193 --> 00:01:51,319
Why?

32
00:01:53,071 --> 00:01:56,074
I've been thinking about it ever since I quit my job.

33
00:01:56,074 --> 00:01:57,867
I wanted to take a break and relax more.

34
00:01:59,828 --> 00:02:00,954
What about me?

35
00:02:02,080 --> 00:02:02,872
Jaemin-ah.

36
00:02:03,123 --> 00:02:05,291
What am I supposed to do?

37
00:02:05,291 --> 00:02:07,335
What did we do yesterday?

38
00:02:07,335 --> 00:02:08,837
You're just going to leave me behind?

39
00:02:08,837 --> 00:02:09,420
Jaemin-ah, well...

40
00:02:09,420 --> 00:02:10,964
I don't even know your name, Hyung.

41
00:02:10,964 --> 00:02:13,133
I know nothing about you.

42
00:02:13,133 --> 00:02:14,217
Wherever you go,

43
00:02:14,217 --> 00:02:15,176
it's not like you'd think of me.

44
00:02:15,176 --> 00:02:16,010
Right?

45
00:02:17,220 --> 00:02:18,138
Let go.

46
00:02:18,304 --> 00:02:19,180
Go.

47
00:02:19,180 --> 00:02:20,723
Just go.

48
00:02:21,099 --> 00:02:23,017
We are nothing to each other,

49
00:02:23,017 --> 00:02:24,227
I guess I was the only one misunderstanding.

50
00:02:26,312 --> 00:02:27,605
It's not like that.

51
00:02:27,814 --> 00:02:29,732
I got carried away all by myself,

52
00:02:31,025 --> 00:02:32,861
wanting to have a celebration party,

53
00:02:32,861 --> 00:02:34,320
and with you, Hyung...

54
00:02:36,489 --> 00:02:38,741
I wanted to get closer.

55
00:02:39,325 --> 00:02:42,996
I wanted to change the name saved as 'Laundromat'.

56
00:02:42,996 --> 00:02:45,331
Not as some stretched-out t-shirt,

57
00:02:45,331 --> 00:02:47,125
but by becoming a decent person,

58
00:02:47,584 --> 00:02:50,587
I wanted to advance my relationship with this person.

59
00:02:50,587 --> 00:02:52,839
The emotions rushing in like a storm

60
00:02:52,839 --> 00:02:55,091
weren't just overwhelming.

61
00:02:55,091 --> 00:02:59,470
Rather, like his familiar fabric softener scent,

62
00:02:59,888 --> 00:03:02,640
they naturally seeped into me.

63
00:03:03,641 --> 00:03:05,101
What am I to you?

64
00:03:06,686 --> 00:03:07,896
I don't know.

65
00:03:09,898 --> 00:03:11,316
The Laundromat?

66
00:03:12,108 --> 00:03:14,027
I'm not in the mood for jokes.

67
00:03:14,611 --> 00:03:16,446
Kang Jiseok.

68
00:03:16,863 --> 00:03:18,114
That's my name.

69
00:03:19,782 --> 00:03:22,368
I'm 34 years old.

70
00:03:22,368 --> 00:03:24,829
I worked at a decent company for 10 years.

71
00:03:26,873 --> 00:03:29,042
And right now, I'm unemployed.

72
00:03:29,042 --> 00:03:29,459
And...

73
00:03:33,046 --> 00:03:34,839
What else should I tell you?

74
00:03:36,841 --> 00:03:39,636
Why are you leaving?

75
00:03:40,136 --> 00:03:42,680
What am I to you, Hyung?

76
00:03:43,348 --> 00:03:46,184
The reason I want to stay in Seoul.

77
00:03:46,643 --> 00:03:50,396
The person who will hold me back.

78
00:03:50,939 --> 00:03:53,316
Will you hold onto me?

79
00:03:58,279 --> 00:04:00,698
Don't go.

80
00:04:01,074 --> 00:04:03,660
There are still so many things I don't know about you.

81
00:04:16,506 --> 00:04:19,467
It was a total pressure interview.

82
00:04:20,593 --> 00:04:23,096
I almost came out without even answering the questions.

83
00:04:23,680 --> 00:04:25,265
So, did you answer well?

84
00:04:25,390 --> 00:04:26,099
Yes!

85
00:04:26,683 --> 00:04:28,434
I told them I had to earn the worth of the clothes.

86
00:04:29,269 --> 00:04:30,144
Huh?

87
00:04:30,603 --> 00:04:32,855
I mean the clothes I borrowed.

88
00:04:32,855 --> 00:04:34,023
Since I have to earn the worth of the clothes,

89
00:04:34,023 --> 00:04:35,817
please pass me!

90
00:04:36,234 --> 00:04:38,111
I almost said that.

91
00:04:45,535 --> 00:04:47,912
I guess I really wanted to see this face.

92
00:04:49,664 --> 00:04:50,957
Huh?

93
00:04:51,249 --> 00:04:52,500
What does that mean?

94
00:04:53,960 --> 00:04:55,878
When I first saw you,

95
00:04:56,254 --> 00:04:59,465
I just found it amusing how your expressions changed so often,

96
00:05:00,091 --> 00:05:03,511
but later, I missed it.

97
00:05:03,511 --> 00:05:05,054
Seeing you smile so brightly.

98
00:05:06,180 --> 00:05:08,683
And a person like that was going to leave?

99
00:05:11,686 --> 00:05:13,521
I was hoping you'd hold onto me.

100
00:05:14,814 --> 00:05:17,734
I was afraid I was the only one misunderstanding,

101
00:05:17,859 --> 00:05:20,445
that my feelings and yours might be different.

102
00:05:20,445 --> 00:05:22,363
I was scared.

103
00:05:23,197 --> 00:05:25,867
Also, my brakes broke down.

104
00:05:27,702 --> 00:05:32,749
My feelings for you couldn't be controlled anymore.

105
00:05:32,749 --> 00:05:36,586
So, just like how I ran away from my company,

106
00:05:36,586 --> 00:05:39,005
I was planning to run away again.

107
00:05:40,965 --> 00:05:44,177
With someone I have no feelings for,

108
00:05:44,177 --> 00:05:46,012
I don't do things like kissing.

109
00:05:49,182 --> 00:05:51,142
I'm not the type to just give my body and heart

110
00:05:51,142 --> 00:05:53,686
away so easily.

111
00:06:13,581 --> 00:06:15,333
It's a congratulatory gift for getting the job.
